# ============================================================
# LabVault repository — what NOT to commit
# ============================================================
#
# This repo holds STRUCTURAL artifacts only:
#   - templates, schemas, dashboards, registry, README
#
# It must NEVER hold real lab data. Real entries live in a
# separate Obsidian vault outside this repo.
#
# These rules are defensive — designed to catch accidents.
# ============================================================

# Block any actual lab/imaging/report data folders if accidentally
# created in this repo. The structural artifact uses subfolders like
# v1/, v2/, docs/ — never Labs/, Imaging/, Reports/ at the repo root.
/Labs/
/Imaging/
/Reports/
**/Labs/
**/Imaging/
**/Reports/

# Block any markdown file that looks like a dated draw note
# (YYYY-MM-DD-*.md in any subfolder of v*/)
v*/Labs/**/*.md
v*/Imaging/**/*.md
v*/Reports/**/*.md

# Allow the example draw note ONLY if it's named with the
# explicit "example" prefix (so accidents are loud)
!**/example_*.md

# OS / editor cruft
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.obsidian/workspace*
.obsidian/cache
*.swp
*~

# Python venvs (in case you add scripts later)
venv/
.venv/
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# Anything explicitly marked private
*PRIVATE*
*private*
*.private.*
